# Jest coverage output (generated by `npm run test:coverage` and the `ci:test` gate); never committed
coverage/
# Playwright baseline & post-migration parity artifacts are a COMMITTED deliverable
# (see e2e-react/). Never ignore them; do NOT use Playwright's default test-results/ dir.
!e2e-react/artifacts/
# ...but the committed deliverable is the screenshots (*.png) + recordings (*.webm)
# ONLY (mirroring artifacts/baseline/, which contains zero traces). Playwright's
# per-test trace archives are large (~2.5 MB each; ~140 MB across the full suite)
# debug artifacts, and its `.last-run.json` is an ephemeral run pointer — neither
# is parity evidence, so keep both out of git. These file-level rules come AFTER
# the `!e2e-react/artifacts/` un-ignore so they take precedence for these names.
e2e-react/artifacts/**/trace.zip
e2e-react/artifacts/**/.last-run.json
